familycare and medical leave (fml) is available to eligible employees in accordance with the federal family and medical leave act (fmla), the california family rights act (cfra) and collective bargaining unit agreements. fml may be used for yourself or an eligible family member.upon completion of fml, you are entitled to return to the same or similar position with equivalent benefits, pay and conditions of employment.you are also entitled to retain any health insurance benefits during time away from work due to fml.see thefamily medical leave (fml) information sheet [pdf]for additional information.complete thecertification of qualifying exigency for military family leave (fml) [pdf]and forward to the leave program manager along with thecertification of serious injury or illness of covered service member military family leave (fml) [pdf].complete thereturn to work certification [pdf]and forward to the leave program manager. you may not return to work without the approval of the leave program manager.for additional information contactup-leaves@sjsu.edu.university-personnel@sjsu.eduup north:408-924-2450up south:408-924-2250up webmasterup northadministration building 242up southupd building 3rd floor